items.body:
Sets/Gets a value into/from cache.

```js
CACHE(key, [value], [expire], [persistent]);
// @key {String} A key.
// @value {Number} A value.
// @expire {String} Expiration
// @persistent {Boolean} Will be persistent?
// returns Object;

var write = CACHE('somekey', 'somevalue', '5 days');
var read = CACHE('somekey');
```

Clears an instance of `setTimeout2`

```js
clearTimeout2(name);
// @name {String} A timeout name.
// returns undefined;
```

This method converts values in object according to the schema and it's effective.

- supports all types like `SchemaBuilder`
- supports Array `tags:[String]`
- undefined properties are removed

```js
CONVERT(obj, name);
// @obj {Object} Object to convert
// @name {String} A schema declaration.
// returns Object;

// For example:
// query = { page: '1', limit: '5', created: '182732837' };
var filter = CONVERT(query, 'page:Number, limit:Number, search:String');
console.log(filter);

// Output:
// { page: 1, limit: 5, search: '' };
```

Alias for `F.cors()`. Creates CORS for a specific URL. Example:

```js
CORS(url, [flags], credentials);
// @url {String} A relative URL, supports wildcard (asterix) routing
// @flags {String Array} Additional options. Can contain `methods` (POST,PUT,DELETE,PATH,GET), `origin` (has to start with http:// or https://) and other values are `headers`. If the item in the array will be Boolean --> this will be a value for `credentials`
// @credentials {Boolean} Allow credentials (cookies)
// returns Framework;

// Enables CORS for:
CORS('/api/*', ['GET', 'POST', 'PUT', 'https://www.totaljs.com'], true);

// Enables CORS for all routes, methods and origins
// +v3.0.0
CORS();

// Allows all method with credentials
// +v3.0.0
CORS('/api/*', true);

// Allows all method without credentials
CORS('/api/*');
```

This method decrypts a value according to the request meta information. The method returns decoded `Object` or `String`.

```js
DECRYPTREQ(req, val, [key]);
// @req {Request} A request object
// @val {Object/String} A value for encrypting
// @key {String} A custom key. The key is combined with `secret`.
// returns Object/String;
```

This method encrypts a value according to the request meta information. In addition it stores user-agent (always) and IP address (in strict mode only). It's targeted for storing encrypted values in e.g. cookies (for temporary usage). __IMPORTANT__: don't use this method for encrypting long-term values in DB. The method returns encoded `String`.

```js
ENCRYPTREQ(req, val, [key], [strict]);
// @req {Request} A request object
// @val {Object/String} A value for encrypting
// @key {String} A custom key. The key is combined with `secret`.
// @strict {Boolean} Enables strict comparing, this means that IP address will be encrypted and compared too.
// returns String;
```

Creates a fallback for non-existing files. __IMPORTANT__: method can process only the one action, so it rewrites previous action if it's defined.

```js
FILE404(action);
// @action {Function(req,res)} A custom action.
```

Writes the message into the specific log file. The log file will contain date + time.

```js
LOGGER(filename, [param..1], [param..2], [param..n]);
// @filename {String} The filename.
// @param..1 {Any} A dynamic parameter.
// @param..2 {Any} A dynamic parameter.
// @param..n {Any} A dynamic parameter.
```

Alias for `F.map()`.

```js
MAP(url, filename, [extension]);
// @url {String} A relative url
// @filename {String} The filename for response
// @extension {String Array} The filter for file extension. This argument can be `Function` as filter
// returns Framework;
```

The method extends flags in the all routes in the function scope like this:

```js
GROUP([flags], action);
// @flags {String or Array/String} Route flags
// @action {Function} A group scope
// returns Framework;

exports.install = function() {

	GROUP(['#middleware', 'authorize'], function() {
		ROUTE('PUT  /api/posts/', someaction);
		ROUTE('POST /api/commnets/', someaction);
		WEBSOCKET('/', chat);
	});

	// IMPORTANT: prefix must contain a slash char "/" 
	GROUP('/urlprefix/', ['flags'], function() {

		ROUTE('PUT  /api/posts/', someaction);
		// OUTPUT WILL BE:
		// "/urlprefix/api/posts/"

		ROUTE('POST /api/commnets/', someaction);
		// OUTPUT WILL BE:
		// "/urlprefix/api/commnets/"

		WEBSOCKET('/', chat);
		// OUTPUT WILL BE:
		// "/urlprefix/"
	});

	GROUP('authorize', function() {
		// Appends "authorize" flag to all nested routes:
		ROUTE('/api/posts/', someaction);
		ROUTE('/api/commnets/', someaction);
	});

}
```

It prepares and validates data according to the schema.

```js
MAKE(schema, model, [callback/$/controller], [novalidate])
// @schena {String} A schema name
// @model {Object}
// @callback {Function/$/Controller} optional
// @novalidate {Boolean} disables validation (default: false)
// returns Promise;
```

__Example__:

```js
yourschema.setSave(async function($, model) {
	// It supports auto handling errors by using "$" argument as the callback
	var data = await MAKE('anotherschema', model.data, $);
});
```

```js
yourschema.setSave(function($, model) {
	MAKE('anotherschema', model.data, function(err, response) {

		if (err) {
			$.invalid(err);
			return;
		}

		// do something

	});
}
```

Registers a new motificator.

```js
MODIFY(fn);
// @fn {Function(type,filename,value,controller)} A processor

MODIFY(function(type, filename, value, controller) {
	// @type {String} can contain: "view", "style", "script", "static" (static files like html, js, script, style, markdown or plain-text files)
	// @filename {String} can be empty
	// @value {String} a content (view, JS, CSS, etc.)
	// @controller {Object} can be "undefined"

	// MUST RETURN (UPDATED) VALUE
	return value;
});
```

Gets the model. This function is the alias for `F.model()`.

```js
MODEL(name);
// @name {String} Modul name.
// returns Object;
```

Gets the module. This function is the alias for `framework.module()`.

```js
MODULE(name);
// @name {String} A name.
// returns Object;
```

Alias for `F.removeListener()` and `F.removeAllListeners()`. Removes all event listeners.

```js
OFF(name, [callback]);
// @name {String} Event name
// @callback {Function} A callback function
// returns Framework;
```

Alias for `F.on()`. Registers a new listener for the event.

```js
ON(name, callback);
// @name {String} Event name
// @callback {Function} A callback function
// returns Framework;
```

Alias for `F.once()`. Registers a new listener for the event.

```js
ONCE(name, callback);
// @name {String} Event name
// @callback {Function} A callback function
// returns Framework;
```

This method wraps `require()` method by adding a path of current application directory.

```js
REQUIRE(path);
// @path {String} A relative path
// returns Object;
``` 

__Example:__

```js
var controller = REQUIRE('controllers/default');
```

Gets the value from `framework.resource()`.

```js
RESOURCE([name], key);
// @name {String} The resource name.
// @key {String} The key.
// returns Object;
```

Can read and store data in Session. Read more in `Additional/Session` section.

```js
SESSION([name], [ondata]);
// @name {String} A session name
// @ondata {Function} A handler for reading data from DB
// returns Object;
```

Creates an instance of `setTimeout`, but if the method is executed multiple times then the timeout is reset

```js
setTimeout2(name, fn, timeout, [limit], [arg]);
// @name {String} A timeout name
// @fn {Function([arg])} callback
// @timeout {Number} A timeout
// @limit {Number} A canceling limit
// @arg {Object} A helper argument
// returns undefined;
```

To clear the timeout:

```js
clearTimeout2(name);
```

Creates object like this `{ success: Boolean, [value: value ]}`. This method is helpful for JSON responses and you can rewrite it.

```js
SUCCESS(success, [value]);
// @success {Boolean} Is success?
// @value {Object} Additional value.
// returns Object;

var obj;

obj = SUCCESS(true);
console.log(obj); // --> obj = { success: true }

obj = SUCCESS(true, 'some value');
console.log(obj); // --> obj = { success: true, value: 'some value' }

obj = SUCCESS();
console.log(obj); // –-> function
obj = obj(new Error('ERROR')); // --> obj = { success: false, error: 'ERROR' }
obj = obj(null, 'some value'); // --> obj = { success: true, value: 'some value' }
obj = obj(null); // --> obj = { success: true }
obj = obj(new Error('ERROR'), 'some value'); // --> obj = { success: true, error: 'ERROR', value: 'some value' }
```

Renders a view into the string. This method simulates the controller and renders HTML into the string.

```js
VIEW(name/url, [model], [layout], [repository], [language]);
// @name/url {String} The view name or URL address
// @model {Object} A model for this view
// @layout {String} A layout for the view
// @repository {Object} A repository object
// @language {String} Localization for the view
// returns String;
```

Compiles and renders a string as view. This method simulates the controller and renders HTML into the string

```js
VIEWCOMPILE(html, [model], [layout], [repository], [language], [key]);
// @html {String} A view markup
// @model {Object} A model for this view
// @layout {String} A layout for the view
// @repository {Object} A repository object
// @language {String} Localization for the view
// @key {String} A cache key.
// returns String;
```

Alias for `U.wait()`.

```js
WAIT(validator, callback, [timeout], [interval]);
// @validator {Function()} has to return BooleanThe validator. It is execute when expire the interval (and multiple times).
// @callback {Function(err, success)} Error handling
// @timeout {Number} Timeout for waiting.
// @interval {Number} Watching interval.
// returns Boolean;
```

Runs a worker. In other words: another script in a __new thread__. This worker returns a buffer from `stdout` in the callback, so `console.log()` in the worker will be as a response in the callback.

```js
WORKER2(name, [args], [callback], [timeout]);
// @name {String} Name of worker (workers/{name}.js).
// @args {Array String} Additional process arguments process.argv.
// @callback {Function(err,buffer)} A callback function
// @timeout {Number} Worker timeout.
// returns ChildProcess;
```

Gets Builders (schema, error, pagination, etc.).

```js
Builders;
// returns Builders;
```

Gets a controller prototype for extending.

```js
Controller;
// returns FrameworkController;
```

Is the framework running in debug mode?

```js
DEBUG;
// returns Boolean;
```

Contains preddefined values or behaviour for some operations.

```js
DEF;
// returns Object;
```

This property can define a currency formatter:

```js
DEF.currencies;
// returns Object;

DEF.currencies.eur = function(val) {
    return val.format(2) + ' &euro;';
};

// Usage:
console.log((1023).currency('eur'));
```

This property stores helper functions for the view engine.

```js
DEF.helpers;
// returns Object;
```
__Example__:

```
DEF.helpers.sum = function(a, b) {
    return a + b;
};
```

View:

```
<div>@{sum(10, 10)} === 20</div>
```

This method tracks a real end of the stream/response/request (it waits for it). Method contains `FINISHED` and `DESTROY` method together. Why? https://github.com/joyent/node/issues/9429

```js
CLEANUP(stream, [callback]);
// @stream {Stream} It can be a Stream, Response or Request.
// @callback {Function()}
// returns undefined;
```

### Example:

```
var Fs = require('fs');
var stream = Fs.createReadStream('some-file.dat');
CLEANUP(stream);
```

The property returns sealed empty array. Very effective for CPU and memory consumption.

```js
EMPTYARRAY;
// returns Array;
```

The property returns sealed empty instance of controller.

```js
EMPTYCONTROLLER;
// returns Object;
```

The property returns sealed empty object. Very effective for CPU and memory consumption.

```js
EMPTYOBJECT;
// returns Object;
```

This method destroy the stream/response/request. Why? https://github.com/joyent/node/issues/9429

```js
DESTROY(stream);
// @stream {Stream} A source: Stream/Response/Request.
// returns undefined;
```

### Example:

```
var Fs = require('fs');
var stream = Fs.createReadStream('some-file.dat');

FINISHED(stream, function(err) {
	console.log('This stream is really finished.');
	DESTROY(stream);
});
```

Returns __ErrorBuilder__ class.

```js
ErrorBuilder;
// returns ErrorBuilder;
```

Gets the framework __instance__.

```js
F;
// returns Framework;
```

Returns __FrameworkImage__ class.

```js
Image;
// returns Image;
```

Is the process executed as a worker?

```js
isWORKER;
// returns Boolean;
```

Creates a NOOP callback function with internal error handling. name (optional) can define a current location for better error handling. For example:

```js
ERROR(name);
// @name {String} A current location name
// returns Function;

RESTBuilder.make(function(builder) {
	builder.url('http://127.0.0.1:8005/api/import/');
	// builder.exec(ERROR('api.progress'));
	builder.exec(ERROR());
});
```

Gets the FrameworkMail.

```js
Mail;
// returns FrameworkMail;
```

A global helper object for storing main data of app.

```js
MAIN;
// returns Object;
```

```js
NOW;
// returns Date;
```

This method can track a real end of the stream/response/request. Why? https://github.com/joyent/node/issues/9429

```js
FINISHED(stream, callback);
// @stream {Stream} A source for tracking of end. It can be a Stream, Response or Request.
// @callback {Function(err)}
// returns undefined;
```

### Example: 

```
var Fs = require('fs');
var stream = Fs.createReadStream('some-file.dat');

FINISHED(stream, function(err) {
	console.log('This stream is really finished.');
	DESTROY(stream);
});
```

Returns __Pagination__ class.

```js
Pagination;
// returns Pagination;
```

Is the framework running in release mode?

```js
RELEASE;
// returns Boolean;
```

A global helper object for storing global data.

```js
REPO;
// returns Object;
```

Can replace `F.onLocale`.

```js
LOCALIZE(fn);
// @fn {Function(req,res)} A localization delegate. A function must return a `language` for the next processing.

LOCALIZE(function(req, res) {
	// req.user
	return 'en';
});

// Is same as older declaration:
F.onLocale = function(req, res) {
	return 'en';
};
```

The controller instance (if exists).

```js
response.controller;
// returns Controller;
```

The request instance.

```js
response.req;
// returns Request;
```

Is the response sent?

```js
response.success;
// returns Boolean;
```

Sends a binary response.

```js
Response.binary(buffer, contentType, [type], [download], [headers]);
// @buffer {Buffer} The buffer
// @contentType {String} The content-type
// @type {String} Transformation type, e.g. `binary`, `utf8`, `ascii`
// @download {String} A download name (creates header with `Content-Disposition`)
// @headers {Object} Additional headers
// returns Response;
```

Sends a custom content.

```js
Response.content(code, body, type, [compress], [headers]);
// @code {Number} A response code
// @body {String} A response body
// @type {String} The content-type
// @compress {Boolean} Disallows GZIP compression for the content
// @headers {Object} Additional headers
// returns Response;
```

Continues in processing of the request.

```js
Response.continue([callback]);
// @callback {Function} A callback function
// returns Response;

// The JPEG counter
	function some_file_routing_action(req, res, isValidation) {
	if (isValidation)
		return req.url.lastIndexOf('.jpg') !== -1;

	// Insert into database
	DATABASE('jpg_counter').insert({ datecreated: new Date(), ip: req.ip });

	// The framework responds on the request automatically.
	res.continue();    
}
```

Sets the value into the cookie. For reading cookies use Request.cookie(). The __default path__ is /.

```js
Response.cookie(name, value, expiration, [options]);
// @name {String} Cookie name
// @value {String} A value
// @expiration {String/Date} The expiration. E.g. "2 days"
// @options {Object} Additional options. Supported values: domain (String), path (String), secure (Boolean), httponly (Boolean), security (String - lax or strict). Default cookie path: "/".
// returns Response;
```

__Cookie options__:

```
{ expires: Date, domain: String, path: String, secure: Boolean, httpOnly: Boolean }
```

Retrieves the values from the HTTP body (POST/PUT method)

```js
request.body;
// returns Object;
```

Sends a file.

```js
Response.file(filename, [download], [headers], [callback]);
// @filename {String} The absolute filename
// @download {String} A download name
// @headers {Object} Additional headers
// @callback {Function} A callback function
// returns Response;
```

Get extension of static file, e.g. `png` or `jpg` (without `.` dot)

```js
request.extension;
// returns String;
```

Retrieves the files from the HTTP body (POST/PUT method with `multipart/form-data` content-type)

```js
request.files;
// returns HttpFile Array;
```

The request flags

```js
request.flags;
// returns String Array;
```

Sends a image.

```js
Response.image(input, make, [headers], [callback]);
// @input {String/Stream} Input can be filename or ReadableStream
// @make {Function(image,res)} Function to processed
// @headers {Object} Custom headers
// @callback {Function} A callback function
