Gets the `content-type` from the base64 string. Example:

```js
String.base64ContentType();
// returns String;

console.log('data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAADIA...'.base64ContentType())
```

Creates a buffer from Base64.

```js
String.base64ToBuffer();
// returns String;
```

Creates the file from base64 string.

```js
String.base64ToFile(filename, [callback]);
// @filename {String} The filename.
// @callback {Function(err)} The callback
// returns String;
```

Capitalize the first letter of string (eg : test -> Test)

```js
String.capitalize([first]);
// @first {Boolean} Capitalize only the first char.
// returns String;
```

Counts word in the string.

```js
String.count(word);
// @word {String} The word to count.
// returns String;
```

Converts the string to `CRC32`.

```js
String.crc32([unsigned]);
// @unsigned {Boolean} Unsigned option
// returns String;
```

Decodes the string from the HTML safe characters.

```js
String.decode();
// returns String;
```

Decrypts the string according to the key.

```js
String.decrypt(key, [secret]);
// @key {String} The key for decoding.
// @secret {String} A secret.
// returns String;
```

Encodes the string to the HTML safe characters.

```js
String.encode();
// returns String;
```

Encrypts the string according to the key.

```js
String.encrypt(key, unique, [secret]);
// @key {String} A key.
// @unique {Boolean} The result will be unique.
// @secret {String} A secret.
// returns String;
```

Checks if the string ends with text.

```js
String.endsWith(value, [ignoreCase]);
// @value {String} The value for compare.
// @ignoreCase {Boolean} Ignores the case sensitive.
// returns Boolean;
```

Formatting the string like `C#`. Example:

```js
String.format([param..1], [param..2], [param..n]);
// @param..1 {String} A dynamic parameter.
// @param..2 {String} A dynamic parameter.
// @param..n {String} A dynamic parameter.
// returns Object;

console.log('My name is {0} {1}'.format('Peter', 'Širka'));
```

Parses the unicode (HTML) characters.

```js
String.fromUnicode();
// returns String;
```

Creates the hash from the string. Supports: `sha1`, `sha256`, `sha512`, `md5`, `crc32` or `crc32unsigned`.

```js
String.hash([type], [salt]);
// @type {string} empty = fast-type (is used in localization), sha1, sha256, sha512, md5, crc32 or crc32unsigned
// @salt {string} A salt which will be added into the end of the string
// returns String;

var string = 'Something'.hash();
var string = 'Something'.hash(true); // +v3.3.0 returns unsigned int
```

Checks if the string contains a valid Base64

```js
