// returns String;
```

Converts the string to `MD5`.

```js
String.md5([salt]);
// @salt {string} Salt for hash.
// returns String;
```

A characters padding - left.

```js
String.padLeft(max, [char]);
// @max {Number} The maximum characters.
// @char {String} The character to fill.
// returns String;
```

A characters padding - right.

```js
String.padRight(max, [char]);
// @max {Number} The maximum characters.
// @char {String} The character to fill.
// returns String;
```

Simple string templating.

```js
String.params(obj);
// @obj {Object} The object for binding of values.
// returns String;

var string = 'My name is {{ name }} and I have {{ age }} years old. Created: {{ created | dd.MM.yyyy }} and credits: {{ credits | ## ### }} credits.'
console.log(string.params({ name: 'Peter', age: 31, created: new Date(), credits: 1000 }));
```

Alias for `String.parseBool`.

```js
