This method modifies documents according to the `data` argument in database. The method doesn't replace entire document, only it updates declared fields.

```js
database.modify(data, [upsert]);
// @data {Object} Data for modification 
// @upsert {Boolean/Object} optional (default: false)
// returns QueryBuilder;
```

__Example__:

```js
NOSQL('users').modify({ name: 'Peter' }).where('email', 'petersirka@gmail.com');
```

- `upsert: true` performs inserting if database doesn't update any documents
- `upsert: Object` performs inserting of `value` of `upsert` argument if database doens't update any documents
- `upsert` can be combined with [`QueryBuilder.insert()`](/total4/407fd001oh51c/#4d25a001mh51c) method

### Atomic operations

- `+key: value` increments a number about defined value
- `-key: value` decrements a number about defined value
- `/key: value` divides a number about defined value
- `*key: value` multiples a number about defined value
- `!key: true` performs toggle for Boolean values
- `<key: value` performs `Math.max(doc[key], value)`
- `>key: value` performs `Math.min(doc[key], value)`

__Example__:

```js
// Increases all prices in "products" db by adding 100
NOSQL('products').modify({ '+price': 100 }); 

// Multiples all prices in "products" db by adding 1.2
NOSQL('products').modify({ '*price': 1.2 }); 

// Performs toggle for "disabled" field
NOSQL('products').modify({ '!disabled': true }); 
```

