```js
builder.insert(fn);
// @fn {Function(doc)} A modificator. This function can modify an object as a reference type. You don't need to `return` some value.
// returns QueryBuilder;
```

__Example__:

```js
var user = {};
user.id = 100;
user.name = 'Peter';

NOSQL('users').modify(user, true).where('id', user.id).insert(function(doc) {
	// "user" not found
	// "doc" is the document which is used in "modify" method
	doc.dtcreated = new Date();
});
```

Joins database with another database. `QueryBuilder.join()` returns a new instance of `QueryBuilder` and a bit modified by adding `.on()` method for creating of relation between databases.

< __IMPORTANT__<br>Joins can't be used for updating/removing operations.

```js
builder.join(field, database, [type]);
// @field {String} A field which will contain a linked data
// @database {String} A database name (more in Database types)
// @type {String} a join type (more in Join types)
// returns QueryBuilder;
```

__Database types__:

- `database.join(name)` performs join with current type of database
- `NOSQL()....join('table/users')` joins `NOSQL` database with `TABLE`
- `TABLE()....join('nosql/users')` joins `TABLE` database with `NOSQL`

__Join types__:

- `left` (default) performs `left join` - right side may not exists
- `inner` performs `inner join` - right side must exist

### One to One

```
var builder = NOSQL('orders').find();
builder.where('paid', true);
builder.take(10);
builder.callback(function(err, docs) {
	// Orders
	console.log(docs);
});

var join = builder.join('user', 'users');
// users.id === orders.userid
join.on('id', 'userid');

// we want only the one document (not array)
join.first();
```

### One to Many

```
var builder = NOSQL('users').find();
builder.take(10);
builder.callback(function(err, docs) {
	// Users with orders
	console.log(docs);
});

var join = builder.join('orders', 'orders');
// orders.id === users.userid
join.on('userid', 'id');

// Orders must be paid
join.where('paid', true);
```

### Scalar operations

__We want to know a min/max/sum price from orders per user:__

```
var builder = NOSQL('users').find();
builder.take(10);
builder.callback(function(err, docs) {
	// Users
	console.log(docs);
});

var join = builder.join('orders', 'orders');
// orders.id === users.userid
join.on('userid', 'id');
join.scalar('price');
```

