Sets a default transformation for all instances of ErrorBuilder.

```js
ErrorBuilder.setDefaultTransform(name);
// @name {String} A transformation name
```

Adds a new transformation for all ErrorBuilders.

```js
ErrorBuilder.addTransform(name, fn, [def]);
// @name {String} A transformation name
// @fn {Function(isresponse)} A transformation function, this function must return transformed object or string
// @def {Boolean} Sets this transformation as default for all instances of ErrorBuilder
// returns Object;
```

__Example:__

```
ErrorBuilder.addTransform('plaintext', function(isresponse) {

	// @isresponse {Boolean} means that the result must be string

	if (isresponse) {
		// Default content-type is always JSON format, but
		// in this case we want plain-text response
		this.setContentType('text/plain');
	}

	var builder = [];

	for (var i = 0; i < this.items.length; i++) {
		var err = this.items[i];
		// err.name
		// err.error
		// err.path
		// err.index
		builder.push(err.error);
	}

	return isresponse ? builder.join(';') : builder; 
});

ErrorBuilder.addTransform('customjson', function(isresponse) {

	var builder = [];

	for (var i = 0; i < this.items.length; i++) {
		var err = this.items[i];
		// err.name
		// err.error
		// err.path
		// err.index
		builder.push({ code: err.name, body: err.error });
	}

	return isresponse ? JSON.stringify(builder) : builder; 
});
```

If `isresponse` argument is `true` then the transformation must return `string`.

HTTP Status code if the ErrorBuilder is used as response.

