// @groupfield {String}
// @datefield {String}
// @scalarfield {String}
// @type {String} optional
// returns QueryBuilder;
```

__Supported types__:

- `hourly`
- `daily` is __default__
- `monthly` 
- `yearly`

__Example__:

```js
NOSQL('apps').stats('url', 'dtcreated', 'memory', 'monthly').callback(function(err, response) {
	console.log(response);
});
```

__Output__:

```js
{
	'https://www.totaljs.com': {
		'201701': { min: 46, max: 60, count: 19 },
		'201702': { min: 44, max: 61, count: 28 },
		'201703': { min: 42, max: 63, count: 31 }
	},
	...
	...
}
```

__Good to know__:

- `date` keys are serialized as:
	- `hourly` key will be in the form `yyyyMMddHH`
	- `daily` key will be in the form `yyyyMMdd`
	- `monthly` key will be in the form `yyyyMM`
	- `yearly` key will be in the form `yyyy`

Expression must be a link to a function. This function will be executed if the `ui-bind` __path__ will be changed.

```html
<ui-bind path="some.path" config="exec:myfunction"></ui-bind>

<script>
	function myfunction(value, path, element) {
		console.log('VALUE HAS BEEN CHANGED:', value);
	}
</script>
```

`+v17` Executes method when the binder is initialized. This command is performed only one time.

```html
<ui-bind path="some.path" config="init:link_to_method"></ui-bind>

<script>
	function link_to_method(value, path, element) {
		// do something
	}
</script>
```

`+v18` Expression must be a link to a function. This function will be executed if __the element is visible__ and the `ui-bind` __path__ will be changed.

```html
<ui-bind path="some.path" config="refresh:myfunction"></ui-bind>

<script>
	function myfunction(value, path, element) {
		console.log('VALUE OF VISIBLE ELEMENT HAS BEEN CHANGED:', value);
	}
</script>
```

*Optional*. A method according to the value of `make` will be executed before the content will be imported. The method __must return updated response__. If the method returns `empty` or `nullable` value then the content won't be imported and used.

```html
<div data-import="url:/someform.html;make:updatesomething"></div>

<script>
	function updatesomething(response, el, path) {
		// @response {String} a response
		// @el {jQuery} a current DOM element wrapped in jQuery
		// @path {String} a declared path

		// IMPORTANT:
		return response + '<div>MY ADDITIONAL CONTENT</div>';
	}
</script>
```

This method internally caches count of executing of this method according to the request IP address. The method can be helpful in `sign-in` process or in `registration`.

```js
BLOCKED($, [limit], [expiration]);
// @$ {SchemaOptions/OperationOptions/TaskOptions/AuthOptions/Controller}
// @limit {Number} a limit for max. executing of this method (default: 5)
// @expiration {String} an expiration (default: '15 minutes')
// returns Boolean;
```

__Example__:

```js
schema.addWorkflow('login', function($) {

	if (BLOCKED($)) {
		$.invalid('error-blocked');
		return;
	}

	// ...
	// ...

});
```

< __Good to know__:<br>If the `limit` is `-1` or `null` then the `IP address` will be removed from the blacklist.

