// @expiration {String} in the form e.g. "5 minutes", "1 day", etc.
// returns db;
```

- all result data will be stored under `key`

### Usage

```js
schema.setQuery(function($) {
	var db = DBMS();
	db.find('tbl_product').where('isremoved=FALSE').take(100);
	db.cache('products', '5 minutes');
	db.callback($.callback);
});
```

### Refresh / Clear cache

- cache can be clear easily from everywhere in your code
- everything depends on the `key`

```js
db.cache('key', 'clear');
```

A global helper object for storing global functions.

