Registers a proxy, so the current web server will be used as a proxy for the specific path.

> __IMPORTANT:__<br>Proxy `endpoint` transfers all requests starting with the path defined in the `endpoint` argument.

```js
PROXY(endpoint, hostname, [copypath], [before], [after], [timeout]);
// @endpoint {String} A relative endpoint, e.g. /users/
// @hostname {String} A hostname with path, e.g. https://www.totaljs.com/users/
// @copypath {Boolean} Copies URL path to a proxy endpoint (default: true)
// @before {Function(uri, req, res)} This function will be evaluated before is proxy applied
// @after {Function(res)} This function will be evaluated after is proxy applied
// @timeout {Number} A timeout in milliseconds (default: 10000)
```

__Example__:

```js
PROXY('/users/', 'https://www.totaljs.com/', function(uri, req, res) {
	// @uri {Object} Prepared URL address
	// @req {Request} Incoming request
	// @res {Response} A response for incoming request
	uri.headers['x-token'] = '123456';
	// uri.path {String} contains target endpoint path to the proxy server
});
```

__Example `copypath:true`__:

```js
PROXY('/users/', 'https://www.totaljs.com/', true);
// "/users/" refers to "https://www.totaljs.com/users/"
// "/users/orders/" refers to "https://www.totaljs.com/users/orders/"
```

__Example `copypath:false`__:

```js
PROXY('/users/', 'https://www.totaljs.com/', false);
// "/users/" refers to "https://www.totaljs.com/"
// "/users/orders/" refers to "https://www.totaljs.com/"
```

__Advanced example__:

```js
PROXY('/users/', 'https://www.totaljs.com/', function(uri, req) {
	// You can change proxy "endpoint" dynamically: 
	uri.path = '/something/?success=1';
});
```

