__Chunker__ is a beneficial tool for storing temporary data when you are importing some data from different services or databases. It can keep a defined count of documents/data (serialized in JSON) per file, and after the import is done, you can browse data step-by-step. __Chunker__ is defined in __FrameworkUtils__ and here is a simple usage:

< __IMPORTANT__: Chunker stores items to different files. A chunker `name` is the name of the file. If the chunker is destroyed, then the background removes all files automatically.

::: Example

```js
var chunker = U.chunker('products', 50);
// chunker === instance

somestream.on('data', U.streamer('<product>', '</product>', function(value, index) {

	var product = value.parseXML();

	// The chunker creates multiple files with a maximum count of chunks/items (in this case: 50 products)
	chunker.write(product);

}));

somestream.on('end', function() {

	// Flushs buffer
	chunker.end();

	chunker.each(function(items, next, index) {

		console.log(chunker.percentage);

		// here we can update DB

		// ....
		// ....

		// Read next items
		next();

	}, function() {

		// This method is called if the chunker doesn't contain any other items (optional).

		// Cleans up hdd (removes all files) and memory
		chunker.destroy();

	});

});
```
:::

Data-Reader is a special part of the Total.js framework; with this reader, you can filter, paginate, and perform scalar operations for `Array` objects. Reader uses `TextDB` reader.

::: Simple example

```js
// Creates Data-Reader instance
var reader = U.reader([{ name: 'Peter', age: 37 }, { name: 'Lucia', age: 39 }, ...]);

// Adds reader
reader.find().between('age', 30, 40).callback(console.log);
```
:::

::: Streaming example

```js
// Creates Data-Reader instance
var reader = U.reader();

// Adds reader
reader.find().where('min', '<', 100).fields('min,dtcreated').callback(function(err, response, meta) {
	console.log(err, response, meta);
});

// Adds reader
reader.find().fields('min,max,dtcreated').take(100).callback(console.log);

// Adds reader
reader.scalar('min').take(100).callback(console.log);

// Adds reader
reader.count().callback(console.log);

// Data streaming
somestream.on('data', function(data) {
	// Pushes data for filtering:
	reader.push(data);
});

somestream.on('end', function() {
	// Ends reading and evaluates callbacks in all defined readers
	reader.push(null);
});
```

:::

