Creates a custom scrollbar.

```js
SCROLLBAR(element, options);
// @element {jQuery element}
// @options {Object}
// returns {ScrollbarInstance}
```

__Options__:

- `shadow {Boolean}` enables shadows
- `orientation {String}` can be `x` or `y` (default undefined - that means `xy`)
- `visibleX {Boolean}` shows X scrollbar (default: `false`)
- `visibleY {Boolean}` shows Y scrollbar (default: `false`)
- `margin {Number}` a margin for scrollbars
- `marginY {Number}` a margin for vertical scrollbar
- `marginYX {Number}` a margin for X offset of vertical scrollbar
- `marginX {Number}` a margin for horizontal scrollbar
- `marginXY {Number}` a margin for Y offset of horizontal scrollbar
- `marginshadowX {Number}` a margin for shadow in horizontal scrollbar
- `marginshadowY {Number}` a margin for shadow in vertical scrollbar
- `onidle {Function(scrollbar)}` the method will be executed if the scrollbar will be idle
- `onscroll {Function(scrollbar)}` the method will be executed if the scrollbar will scroll
- `onresize {Function(scrollbar)}` the method will be executed if the scrollbar will be resized

This method appends an `Error` to `ErrorBuilder` within the current operation.

```js
$.invalid(name, [error]);
// @name {String}
// @error {String/Number/Error} optional
```

__Example__:

```js
if (!$.user.sa) {

	// Error message will be used from resource file
	$.invalid('401');

	// Number will be convert to a string:
	// $.invalid(401);

	// Raw message:
	// $.invalid('Unauthorized');

	// Localized:
	// $.invalid('@(Unauthorized)');

	// Error message will be "Unauthorized" and error name "401"
	// $.invalid('401', 'Unauthorized');

	return;
}

// ...
// ...
// ...
$.success();
```

