The method runs a simple endpoint test and responds with the simple UI:

![Unit test](/download/7jk6002fw40d-uy2etf-556x139-1.jpg)

```js
// controller.runtest(url, name)
// @url {String} a route URL address with the method
// @name {String} a name of test
// return {Test} Look to Framework/Test section

// OR
// controller.runtest(callback)
// @callback {Function(err, response, output)}

ROUTE('GET /test/', function() {
	var self = this;

	// You can call unlimited count of test
	self.runtest('GET  /api/users/', 'Users.query');
	self.runtest('POST /api/users/', 'Users.insert', (err, value) => value.success === true).body({ name: 'Peter' });

	// Total.js API example:
	self.runtest('API  /apiv1/  users_read');

	// A callback (OPTIONAL)
	// IMPORTANT: this method creates a response automatically, this delegate can clean something
	self.runtest(function(err, response, output) {
		// err {Number} a count of errors
		// response {Array of Responses} from endpoints (indexes = order, starting with 0)
		// output {Array of result} response output which is rendered in the callback
	});
});
```

__Good to know__:

- if you call the test endpoint with the `XHR` header then the response will be serialized into the `JSON` format
- For __Authorized__ `+` vs. __Unauthorized__ `-` access, you need to specify `+` or `-` before HTTP method in the route, for example: `self.runtest('+GET /api/users/')`

