A resource file is a plain-text file with the `.resource` extension stored in the `/resources/` directory. The resource file is a simple `KEY/VALUE` dictionary targeted for creating localization.

< __Total.js framework__ uses __default resource__ called `/resources/default.resource`

- resources are read-only
- resource files stay loaded into memory for some time after being accessed
- `ErrorBuilder` load's error messages from the current resource file according to the `LOCALIZE()` delegate

__Example of resource file__:

```resource
key1           : value1

// comment
key2           : value2
key3           : <b>with the tag</b>
```

## Reading values from resources

You can read values from resource files via the `RESOURCE()` method.

__Node.js side__:

```js
RESOURCE([name], key);
// @name {String} The resource name.
// @key {String} The key.
// returns Object;
```

__View engine__:

```html
@{RESOURCE('key3')}
<!-- Encoded: &lt;b&gt;with the tag&lt;/b&gt; -->

@{!RESOURCE('key3')}
<!-- Raw: <b>with the tag</b> -->

@{RESOURCE('en', 'key3')}
<!-- Encoded: &lt;b&gt;with the tag-en&lt;/b&gt; -->

@{!RESOURCE('en', 'key3')}
<!-- Raw: <b>with the tag-en</b> -->

@{RESOURCE('de', 'key3')}
<!-- Encoded: &lt;b&gt;with the tag-de&lt;/b&gt; -->

@{!RESOURCE('de', 'key3')}
<!-- Raw: <b>with the tag-de</b> -->
```

