The method creates a filter automatically according to the __Total.js Schema__. DBMS will use query parameters for the filtering and parameters:

- `fields` (separated by comma) will be returned from DB
- `page` will be used as a page
- `limit` will be used as a limit otherwise `def_maxlimit`
- `sort` will be used for __sorting__ otherwise `def_sort` (can contain multiple values separated by `,` comma)

```js
// builder.autofill($, allowedfields, skipfields, def_sort, def_maxlimit, [localized]);
// @$ {SchemaOptions} Instance of SchemaOptions
// @allowedfields {String} Optional, can contain fields not defined in the schema and must be separated by comma "," in the form "key:datatype"
// @skippedfields {String} Optional, can contain skip fields defined in schema and must be separated by comma ","
// @def_sort {String} default sort in the form "FIELDNAME_asc" or "FIELDNAME_desc"
// @def_maxlimit {Number} a maximum count of items per page
// @localized {String} Optional, defines localized name of fields
// returns QueryBuilder

// IMPORTANT:
// If "def_maxlimit" is not defined then the pagination isn't applied

// Example:
db.find('users').autofill($, 'dtcreated:Date,dtupdated:Date', 'id', 'dtcreated_desc', 50);

// Example with localized fields:
db.find('users').autofill($, 'dtcreated:Date,dtupdated:Date', 'id', 'dtcreated_desc', 50, 'name,description').language('sk');
```

The method creates a filter automatically according to URL query arguments (in most cases). DBMS will use query parameters for the filtering and parameters:

- `fields` (separated by comma) will be returned from DB
- `page` will be used as a page
- `limit` will be used as a limit otherwise `def_maxlimit`
- `sort` will be used for __sorting__ otherwise `def_sort` (can contain multiple values separated by `,` comma)

```js
// builder.autoquery(query, schema, def_sort, def_maxlimit, [localized]);
// @query {Object} A query object e.g. { fields: 'id,name', sort: 'dtcreated_desc' }
// @schema {String} A custom data schema e.g. 'id:String,name:String,dtcreated:Date'
// @def_sort {String} Default sort in the form "FIELDNAME_asc" or "FIELDNAME_desc"
// @def_maxlimit {Number} A maximum count of items per page
// @localized {String} Defines localized name of fields
// returns QueryBuilder

// IMPORTANT:
// If "def_maxlimit" is not defined then the pagination isn't applied

// Example:
db.find('users').autoquery($.query, 'id:UID,name:string,age:number,dtcreated:date,dtupdated:date', 'dtcreated_desc', 50);

// Example with localized fields:
db.find('products').autoquery($.query, 'id:UID,name:string,description:string,dtcreated:date,dtupdated:date', 'dtcreated_desc', 50, 'name,description').language('sk');
```

