The method creates a request. We recommend to use Total.js `RESTBuilder` for quick usage.

```js
REQUEST(opt, callback);
// @opt {Object} options
// @callback {Function(err, response)}
```

- __required__ `opt.url` {String} URL address
- `opt.encrypt {String}` a key for Total.js `backend/frontend` encryption
- `opt.insecure {Boolean}` enables insecure connection (default: `false`)
- `opt.xhr {Boolean}` appends `XMLHttpRequest` header
- `opt.timeout {Number}` a request timeout in milliseconds, default: `CONF.default_request_timeout {Number}` (`3000`) 
- `opt.encoding {String}` encoding (default: `utf8`)
- `opt.headers {Object}` a custom headers in the form `key:value`
- `opt.method {String}` a request method, must be uppercase (default: `GET`)
- `opt.proxy {String}` a proxy server `hostname:port` or `user:pass@hostname.port`
- `opt.query {Object}` URL query arguments (can be part of URL address)
- `opt.unixsocket {Object}` `.socket: String` and `.path: String`
- `opt.dnscache {Boolean}` enables caching of resolving IP from DNS (default: `false`)
- `opt.noredirect {Boolean}` disables responding to `301` or `302` status
- `opt.keepalive {Boolean}` enables keep-alive connection (default: `false`)
- `opt.body {Object/String}` a request body
- `opt.cookies {Object}` cookies in the form `key:value`
- `opt.cook {Boolean}` response cookies will be parsed and assigned to `opt.cookies`
- `opt.limit {Number}` a limit for response body in bytes
- `opt.custom {Boolean}` returns raw `{ status: Number, stream: Response }` in the callback
- `opt.key {Buffer}` SSL key
- `opt.cert {Buffer}` SSL certificate
- `opt.dhparam {String}` DH parameter
- `opt.nocookies {Boolean}` disables parsing cookies while redirecting
- `opt.ondata {Function(chunks:Buffer, percentage:Number)}` a custom delegate for processing of data
- `opt.onprogress {Function(percentage:Number)}` a custom delegate for processing of data
- `opt.files {Array Object}` file object must be in the form:
	- with absolute path `{ name: 'filename.txt', filename: String }`
	- with a buffer `{ name: 'filename.txt', buffer: Buffer }`
- `opt.type {String}` a custom content type, supports:
	- `plain` text/plain
	- `html` text/html
	- `raw` application/octet-stream
	- `json` application/json
	- `urlencoded` x-www-form-urlencoded
	- `xml` text/xml

__Standard usage__:

```js
var opt = {};
opt.url = 'https://www.totaljs.com';
opt.callback = function(err, response) {

	// response.headers {Object}
	// response.body {String/Object} a response body
	// response.status {Number} status code
	// response.host {String} resolved host name (opt.resolve = true returns IP address)
	// response.cookies {Object} response cookies (nullable)

};

REQUEST(opt);
```

__Unix-socket__:

```js
var opt = {};
opt.unixsocket = { socket: '', path: '' };
opt.callback = function(err, response) {

	// response.headers {Object}
	// response.body {String/Object} a response body
	// response.status {Number} status code
	// response.host {String} resolved host name (opt.resolve = true returns IP address)
	// response.cookies {Object} response cookies (nullable)

};

REQUEST(opt);
```

__Raw response__:

```js
var opt = {};
opt.url = 'https://www.totaljs.com';
opt.custom = true;
opt.callback = function(err, response) {

	// response.status {Number} status code
	// response.headers {Object}
	// response.stream {Response}

};

REQUEST(opt);
```

