This method encrypts a value. __IMPORTANT__: don't use this method for encrypting long-term values in DB. The method returns encoded `String`.

```js
ENCRYPT(value, key, [unique]);
// @value {String/Object} a value to encrypt
// @key {String} a secret key
// @unique {Boolean} optional, always returns unique encrypted value with the same content (default: false)
// returns String;
```

__Example__:

