The method performs comparing of `$.user.permissions` or `$.user.roles` with the `permission` argument. If the user is unauthorized then the method automatically performs `$.invalid(401)`.

- permissions/roles (defined in the argument) are compared with the `$.user.permissions` or `$.user.roles` property
- `$.user.sa {Boolean}` or `$.user.su {Boolean}` is automatically permitted

```js
UNAUTHORIZED($/Controller, permissionA, [permissionB], [permissionN]);
