### Element `<ui-plugin>`

__`<ui-plugin>`__ can simplify paths declaration in HTML code. In other words: plugins can reduce paths in all nested components.

::: How do plugins work?

```html
<!-- WITHOUT PLUGIN -->
<div>
	<ui-component name="input" path="users.form.firstname">Name</ui-component>
	<ui-component name="input" path="users.form.age">Age</ui-component>    
</div>

<!-- WITH PLUGIN -->
<ui-plugin path="users.form">
	<ui-component name="input" path="?.firstname">Name</ui-component>
	<ui-component name="input" path="?.age">Age</ui-component>    
</ui-plugin>
```

- first, you need to implement an <ui-plugin> element with a `path` attribute
- `path` attribute must contain `path` or `?` due to anonymous plugins
:::

::: __Declaration__

```html
<ui-plugin path="PATH" config="CONFIG">
	<!--
		IMPORTANT:
		Inside the plugin element must be declared some <ui-component> or <ui-bind>
		element because the plugin won't be initialized without them.
	-->
</ui-plugin>

EXAMPLE:

<ui-plugin path="users.form" config="init:users_form_init">
	- method "users_form_init" will be evaluated if the plugin will be initialized
</ui-plugin>
```

__Config__:

- `init:path.to.method` evaluates a method when the plugin is initialized `function(plugin, el)`
- `class:class_name` toggles class for the element
- `isolated:true` can enable an isolated plugin (a parent plugin path won't be inherited)
- __NEW__: `aclass:true` adds a plugin path as a class name
- __NEW__: `delay:300` a delay for toggling classes (default: `300`)
:::

::: Isolated plugins with `isolated:true`

Independent plugins can rewrite the current plugin. __Independence__ is enabled by adding `isolated:true` to the plugin config `<ui-plugin path="products.form" config="isolated:true">`.

```html
<ui-plugin path="users.form">

	<ui-component name="textbox" path="?.name">Name</ui-component>
	<!-- path will be: users.form.name -->

	<!-- Isolated plugin -->
	<ui-plugin path="products.form" config="isolated:true">
		<ui-component name="textbox" path="?.name">Name</ui-component>
		<!-- path will be: products.form.name -->
	</ui-plugin>

	<!-- Inherited scope -->
	<ui-plugin path="products.form">
		<ui-component name="textbox" path="?.name">Name</ui-component>
		<!-- path will be: users.form.products.form.name -->
	</ui-plugin>

</ui-plugin>
```
:::

::: Anonymous plugin with `?` question mark in `path` attribute

Anonymous plugins are a very good option for creating reusable independent web parts, e.g. `Contact form`, `Subscriber form`, etc...

- jComponent generates a random path for this plugin
- the path will have more than 15 chars
- the path will be stored in the `window` object
- example: `jmhjxgietazasfazfqxqb`

```html
<ui-plugin path="?">

	<ui-component name="textbox" path="?.name">Name</ui-component>
	<!-- path will be: random_path.name -->

</ui-plugin>

<!-- EXAMPLE -->

<ui-plugin path="?">

	<ui-component name="textbox" path="?.name">Name</ui-component>
	<!-- path will be e.g.: aoyhdvlmloorhzomzm.name -->

</ui-plugin>

<ui-plugin path="?">

	<ui-component name="textbox" path="?.name">Name</ui-component>
	<!-- path will be e.g.: xsngbvdllnidnaownly.name -->

</ui-plugin>
```

__+v18 supports anonymous plugins:__

```html
<ui-plugin path="? contactform" config="init:?/init">

	<ui-component name="textbox" path="?.name">Name</ui-component>
	<!-- path will be e.g.: xsngbvdllnidnaownly.name -->

	<ui-component name="validation" path="?">
		<button name="submit" class="exec" data-exec="?/submit" disabled>SUBMIT</button>
	</ui-component>

</ui-plugin>

<script>

	// Each anonymous plugin with "? contactform" will have own instance of plugin

	PLUGIN('? contactform', function(exports) {

		// exports.scopedata;
		// Contains plugin instance

		exports.init = function() {
			// Plugin is initialized
		};

		exports.submit = function() {
			var model = exports.form;
			// do something
		};

	});

</script>
```

__+v18 improved anonymous plugins with exact path:__

```html
<ui-plugin path="your.absolute.path contactform" config="init:?/init">

	<ui-component name="textbox" path="?.name">Name</ui-component>
	<!-- path will be e.g.: xsngbvdllnidnaownly.name -->

	<ui-component name="validation" path="?">
		<button name="submit" class="exec" data-exec="?/submit" disabled>SUBMIT</button>
	</ui-component>

</ui-plugin>

<script>

	// Each anonymous plugin with "? contactform" will have own instance of plugin

	PLUGIN('? contactform', function(exports) {

		// exports.scopedata;
		// Contains plugin instance

		exports.init = function() {
			// Plugin is initialized
		};

		exports.submit = function() {
			var model = exports.form;
			// do something
		};

	});

</script>
```
:::

::: Special usage with `?` question mark

Plugins supports one more thing. If the component path will contain `?` question mark in the path, then the plugin replaces this `?` symbol with the current plugin path.

```html
<ui-plugin path="users">

	<ui-component name="textbox" path="address.?.street">Street</ui-component>
	<!-- path will be: address.users.street -->

</ui-plugin>
```
:::

::: Skip parent plugin

`+v17` this behavior is targeted for special cases. You can skip parent plugins in the form `?COUNT_OF_SKIP`, the example below describes more:

```html
<ui-plugin path="level1">
	<ui-plugin path="level2">
		<ui-plugin path="level3">

			<ui-bind path="?.name"></ui-bind>
			<!-- Path will be decoded as: level1.level2.level3.name -->

			<ui-bind path="?1.name"></ui-bind>
			<!-- Path will be decoded as: level1.level2.name -->

			<ui-bind path="?2.name"></ui-bind>
			<!-- Path will be decoded as: level1.name -->

		</ui-plugin>
	</ui-plugin>
</ui-plugin>
```
:::

::: __Good to know__
- __IMPORTANT__: plugin must contain some components or binders
- __plugins__ need to be declared in HTML directly
- __plugins__ can have nested plugins, which will inherit paths from parents
:::

### PLUGINS

Plugins are targeted for dynamic parts, which can be removed when they aren't used. Plugins are the best way to handle dynamic pages, forms, windows, etc., in __SPA__ / Single Page Applications. 

< __IMPORTANT__: `events` or `watchers` declared in the plugin will be removed automatically after the plugin has been removed.

### Declarations

::: Plugin declaration

- a plugin `name` can contain `a-z` chars only (no numbers or white characters)

```javascript
PLUGIN('name_of_plugin', function(exports) {

	// You can define your custom functions or properties
	exports.myfunction_1 = function() {

		exports.set('something', 'VALUE');
		// Interally it translates path to:
		// SET('name_of_plugin.something', 'VALUE');

		exports.myfunction_2();
		// exports.myfunction_2(); will evaluate a function defined in the same plugin
	};

	exports.myfunction_2 = function() {
		console.log('something');
	};    

	exports.myfunction_N = function() {
		console.log('something');        
	};

	// 2 way data-binding watcher
	// Path will be targeted to "name_of_plugin.path"
	exports.watch('path', function(value) {
		// ...
	});

	// 2 way data-binding watcher
	// Path will be targeted to "window.absolute.path.to.variable"
	WATCH('absolute.path.to.variable', function(path, value) {
		// ...
	});

	// Events
	ON('some.event', function(req) {
		// ...
	});

});
```
::: 

::: Good to know

- A plugin is removed when the parent element of the `<script>` is removed
- A plugin is removed when the plugin with the same name is initialized again
- [__Example with Plugins__](https://github.com/totaljs/emptyproject-jcomponent)
- [Total.js CMS uses Plugins in the admin area](https://github.com/totaljs/cms)
- Keep __Plugins__ as independent `.html` files
- We recommend using Plugin names with lower-case

:::

::: __NEW__: Pluginables

Pluginables are the same as the plugins and are evaluated only when they are executed via `EXEC()` method. Otherwise, they sleep.

```js
PLUGINABLE(name, declaration, init);
// @name {String} A name of plugin
// @declaration {Function(exports)}
// @init {Function/String Array} optional, an initialization
```

__A simple example__:

```js
PLUGINABLE('accountform', function(exports) {

	exports.alert = function() {
		console.log('ALERT');
	};

});

// The plugin "accountform" will be initialized and evaluated after that:
EXEC('accountform/alert');
```

__Example with initialization method__:

```js
PLUGINABLE('accountform', function(exports) {

	exports.alert = function() {
		console.log('ALERT');
	};

}, function(next) {

	// @next {Function}

	// Async initialization
	// IMPORTANT: next() method must be executed!!!
	setTimeout(next, 1000);

});
```

__Example with middleware__:

```js
PLUGINABLE('accountform', function(exports) {

	exports.alert = function() {
		console.log('ALERT');
	};

}, 'middleware1, middleware2, middleware3');
```

__External pluginables__:

```js
PLUGINABLE('accountform', '/forms/account.html');
```

File `/forms/account.html`:

```js
PLUGINABLE('accountform', function(exports) {

	exports.alert = function() {
		console.log('ALERT');
	};

});
```
:::

Creates a WebSocketClient instance.

```js
WEBSOCKETCLIENT(callback);
// @callback {Function(client)} A callback function
// returns undefined;

WEBSOCKETCLIENT(function(client) {

	// Default options and must be applied before client.connect() is executed
	// client.options.type = 'json';
	// client.options.compress = true;
	// client.options.reconnect = 3000;
	// client.options.encodedecode = false;
	// client.optinos.reconnectserver = false;

	// You can define a custom headers (must be applied before client.connect() is executed)
	// client.headers['x-token'] = 'YOUR-TOKEN'

	// You can define a custom cookies (must be applied before client.connect() is executed)
	// client.cookies.token = 'YOUR-TOKEN';
	// client.cookies.sid = '3adsoeroimx3019239ewiq10293';

	// client.connect(url, [protocol], [origin]);
	client.connect('ws://127.0.0.1:8000/');

	client.on('open', function() {
		console.log('OPEN');
	});

	client.on('close', function() {
		console.log('CLOSE');
	});

	client.on('error', function(e) {
		console.log('ERROR', e);
	});

	client.on('message', function(message) {
		console.log('MESSAGE', message);
	});

	// Sending:
	// client.send({ some: 'object' });

	// Close a connection:
	// client.close([message], [code]);
	// @message {String/Object} a custom message
	// @code {Number} a custom code
	// IMPORTANT: client will get message+code in "onclose" delegate 

	// Destroy Socket
	// client.free();

});
```

__Example__:

```js
NEWSCHEMA('Customers', function(schema) {

	// Output will be an error in the form: "Customer not found"
	schema.addWorkflow('notfound', async function($) {

		var item = await DBMS().read('tbl_customer').id('NOT_FOUND').fields('id,name').error('Customer not found').callback($);

		// IMPORTANT:
		// The framework won't process the code below due to an error thrown by the DBMS module

		item.name = item.name.toUpperCase();
		$.callback(item);
	});

	// Output will be a record {Object} read from DB
	schema.addWorkflow('found', async function($) {

		var item = await DBMS().read('tbl_customer').id('8bcq001fl41d').fields('id,name').error('Customer not found').callback($);

		// OK, we have a record from DB
		// now we can modify it:

		item.name = item.name.toUpperCase();
		$.callback(item);
	});

});
```

The method can import HTML content, JavaScript or CSS from external source.

- supports re-type of extension `https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/js?key=KEY .js`
- styles and scripts are inserted into the HTML head
- supports environments
- `+v16` __NEW__ supports a dependency validator via `<path>` phrase

```js
IMPORT(url, [target], [callback], [insert], [preparator]);
// @url {String or String Array} Relative or Absolute URL address
// @target {String} Optional, jQuery selector (default: "document.body")
// @callback {Function} Optional and the method will be wait for non-exist components
// @insert {Boolean} Optional, inserts the content (default) or "false" will replace the entire content
// @preparator {Function(content)} Optional, needs to return modified content

// Simple usage:
IMPORT('/templates/products.html');

// Content will be inserted to <div id="templates"></div>
IMPORT('/templates/products.html', '#templates');

// With a callback:
IMPORT('/templates/products.html', function() {
    // Done, template is imported and inserted
    // You can manipulate with DOM
});

// With a preparator function
IMPORT('/templates/products.html', NOOP, function(content, response) {
    return content.replace(/logo\.png/i, 'newlogo.png');
});

// Import e.g. scripts
IMPORT('https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/d3/4.10.2/d3.min.js');

// Import some dependency only one!!!
IMPORT('ONCE https://.....');
// or
IMPORT('!https://.....');

// +v16
// Supports dependency validator
// Imports D3 only when d3 is not part of window
IMPORT('<d3> https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/d3/4.10.2/d3.min.js');

// or "path to variable", a negative value will import dependency
IMPORT('<path> https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/d3/4.10.2/d3.min.js');

// or "path to function", a negative value will import dependency
// function will be evaluated as a function
// IMPORTANT: you can't use any argument for the function
IMPORT('<path()> https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/d3/4.10.2/d3.min.js');
```

`+v14.0.0.` Is same as `IMPORT()` method but it needs to contain `expire` argument. This method can't cache plain `css` or `js`.

```js
IMPORTCACHE(url, expire, [target], [callback], [insert], [preparator]);
// @url {String} Relative or Absolute URL address
// @expire {String} Expiration, e.g. 5 minutes
// @target {String} Optional, jQuery selector (default: "document.body")
// @callback {Function} Optional and the method will be wait for non-exist components
// @insert {Boolean} Optional, inserts the content (default) or "false" will replace the entire content
// @preparator {Function(content)} Optional, needs to return modified content
```

