__Example__:

```js
QUERIFY({ name: 'Peter', age: 37, tags: ['a', 'b', 'c'] });
// Output: ?name=Peter&age=37&tags=a%2Cb%2Cc

QUERIFY('https://www.totaljs.com', { name: 'Peter', age: 37, tags: ['a', 'b', 'c'] });
// Output: https://www.totaljs.com?name=Peter&age=37&tags=a%2Cb%2Cc

QUERIFY('API https://www.totaljs.com action_name', { name: 'Peter', age: 37, tags: ['a', 'b', 'c'] });
// Output: API https://www.totaljs.com?name=Peter&age=37&tags=a%2Cb%2Cc action_name
```

Running Total.js application is very easy. You can use the Total.js framework for various cases like providing web applications, services, or some utilities.

__Installation__:

- create a folder where you will have stored all projects
- then install Total.js framework from NPM: `$ npm install total4`
- then follow the instructions below:

