Some of the __Total.js apps__ support __Total.js Extensions__. Extensions are JavaScript scripts that allow you to extend the server-side Total.js app by uploading or adding script directly via UI interface into your Total.js app.

- Total.js v4 `+0.0.50` supports extensions

< :far fa-exclamation-triangle: __WARNING__:<br>Extensions are dangerous because they have full access to the Node.js process. So the extensions can read/create/remove files or affect system behavior.

## Example of an extension script

__Good to know:__ Each application (that supports Extensions) can implement different meta keys.

```js
// Meta information
exports.name = 'My extension';
exports.author = 'Peter Sirka';
exports.icon = 'ti ti-plug';
exports.color = '#4285F4';
exports.version = '1.0.0';
exports.summary = 'This script registers a new route /hello-world/';

// Optional
// A readme file
// exports.readme = 'Markdown';

// A custom config
// exports.config = {};

// Identifier is generated automatically, but you can add enter your own:
// exports.id = 'myextension'; // lower-case and only a-z chars

// Optional
exports.install = function(next) {

	// @next {Function([err])}

	// Here you can perform some steps, this method is executed only once
	// when the extension is registered

	// !!!!!!!!!!
	// IMPORTANT:
	// !!!!!!!!!!

	next();

	// Or failed result:
	// next('Faild to install');
};

// Optional
exports.uninstall = function() {

	// This delegate is executed when the extension is uninstalling or reinstalling

};

exports.make = function() {

	// Installation is done
	// Here you can extend the application


	ROUTE('/hello/', function() {
		this.plain('Hello world!');
	});

};
```

## :far fa-flask: How can I test my extensions?

- [download empty Total.js project](https://github.com/totaljs/emptyproject)
- follow install instructions
- then create a directory `extensions`
- and finally, create an extension file e.g. `myextension.js`
- run the app

## :far fa-question-circle: Good to know

- routes/schemas/operations/middleware/tasks defined in the `exports.install()` or `exports.make()` will be automatically removed when the extenion will be uninstalled

