This method can be used to perform application/database updates. The function will attempt to execute the update scripts sequentially in the specified order. If a file can't be loaded, the update method will continue with the next script. Scripts are running in the main application thread. Only the thread "0"  will perform the update if you execute the update in cluster mode. This feature is a simple alternative to the `startup` folder.

```js
UPDATE(versions, [A callback], [pause_server_message]);
// @versions {String Array} Definion of old version of app
// @A callback {Function(err)} callback
// @pause_server_message {String} A custom message for `PAUSESERVER()`

// How does the framework perform that update?
// - tries to load a script /updates/1.0.1.js
// - tries to load a script /updates/1.0.2.js
// - tries to load a script /updates/1.0.3.js
UPDATE(['1.0.1', '1.0.2', '1.0.3'], function() {
	// DONE
}, 'Updating database');

// After update are files renamed to:
// - tries to load a script /updates/1.0.1.js-bk
// - tries to load a script /updates/1.0.2.js-bk
// - tries to load a script /updates/1.0.3.js-bk
// So after the next start will the scripts skipped.
```

