Registers a new transformation and you can register multiple same transformations. Transformations can be helpful in some pluginable / extensible Total.js apps.

```js
NEWTRANSFORM(name, fn, [id]);
// @name {String} a transformation name
// @fn {Function($)} a processor (read about "$" in "Data models" section)
// @id {String} a custom id (otherwise will be generated automatically)
// returns {String} an identifier of this transformation
```

### Example

__Register a new transformation__:

```js
// UpperCase
NEWTRANSFORM('send', function($, value) {

	// $.value {Object} === @value

	$.value = value.toUpperCase();
	$.next();

});

// Reverse
NEWTRANSFORM('send', function($, value) {

	// $.value {Object} === @value

	$.value = value.split('').reverse().join('');
	$.next();

});
```

__Usage__:

```js
TRANSFORM('send', 'Total.js', function(err, response) {
	console.log(response);
	// Output: SJ.LATOT
});
```

### How to remove transformation?

```js
var id = NEWTRANSFORM('send', function($) {
	...
});

var id = NEWTRANSFORM('send', function($) {
	...
}, 'uppercase');

// The framework removes transformation without "fn" argument
NEWTRANSFORM('send', id);
NEWTRANSFORM('send', 'uppercase');
```

