This event is emitted `ERROR()` method captures an error.

```js
ON('ERROR', function(value) {

	// @value {Array/Object}
	// |--- Array  [{ error: 'Something' }];
	// |--- Object { error: 'Something' };

	console.log(value);

});
```

The method is error handler.

```js
ERROR(response|async, [success], [error]);
// @response {Object/Array/Boolean/Function}
// @success {Function/String} optional, triggered when is not captured error
// @error {Function/String} optional, triggered when is captured error
// returns {Boolean/Function}
```

__New inline implementation in AJAX methods__:

ERROR handler can be used in all AJAX operations in these methods `AJAX()`, `API()`, `TAPI()`, `WAPI()` and `DAPI()`. Usage is simple, e.g. `AJAX('GET /users/ ERROR', '?.something')`

__Inline example__:

```js
if (ERROR(value))
	return;
```

__Async example__:

```js
// Valid response will be assinged to the "?.users" path
TAPI('users ERROR', '?.users');

// Valid response will be assinged to the "?.users" path
// Error will be assigned to the "?.error" path
TAPI('users', ERROR(true, '?.users', '?.error'));

// Valid response will be returned in to the callback "success" delegate
TAPI('users ERROR', function(response) {
	console.log('Users', response);
});

TAPI('users', ERROR(function(response) {
	console.log('success', response);
}, function(response) {
	console.log('error', response);
}));

TAPI('users', ERROR(function(response) {
	console.log('success', response);
}, function(response) {
	console.log('error', response);
}));

TAPI('users', ERROR(true, null, function(response) {
	console.log('error', response);
}));

TAPI('users', ERROR(true, null, '?.error'));
```

< __Good to know__<br>If the method captures and error then it emits `ON('ERROR', function(err) { ...` event.

