Routing is the most commonly used functionality in __Total.js framework__. Via routing, you can route all Requests/WebSockets to specific actions easily. Total.js supports three types of routing:

- [Routing for dynamic content](#)
- [File routing](#)
- [WebSocket routing](#)

In most cases, routes are defined in `/controllers/` directory.

< :far fa-exclamation-triangle: __IMPORTANT__<br>Use relative URL addresses in __lower-case__.

## Routing for dynamic content

This type of routing is used to generate dynamic content like JSON outputs, views, etc... A request is transformed into `Controller` which is used to build a response data. This routing can't contain file extension in the relative URL address because static files are handled via file routing.

```js
// Example
// File: /controllers/example.js

exports.install = function() {

	// Route declaration
	ROUTE('METHOD RELATIVEURL');
	ROUTE('METHOD RELATIVEURL *SCHEMA --> operation');
	ROUTE('METHOD RELATIVEURL *SCHEMA --> operation1 operation2 (response) operation3');
	ROUTE('METHOD RELATIVEURL', action_fn);

};
```

__Real usage__:

```js
// Example
// File: /controllers/example.js

exports.install = function() {

	// View routing
	ROUTE('GET /');
	ROUTE('GET /', 'view_name');

	// Schema routing
	// Example of REST API routing
	// "+" char means that all request must be authorized
	ROUTE('+GET    /api/users/        *Users --> query');
	ROUTE('+GET    /api/users/{id}/   *Users --> read');
	ROUTE('+POST   /api/users/        *Users --> insert');
	ROUTE('+PUT    /api/users/{id}/   *Users --> update');
	ROUTE('+PATCH  /api/users/{id}/   *Users --> patch');
	ROUTE('+DELETE /api/users/        *Users --> remove');

	// Custom routing to a specific function
	ROUTE('GET /', custom_action);

};

function custom_action() {
	// "this" is a "Controller" instance
	this.view('index');
}
```

## How to handle the uploading of files?

- [File upload - example](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/upload-multipart)
- [Documentation `HttpFile`](/total4/40845001ur51c/)

```js
// Example
// File: /controllers/upload.js

exports.install = function() {

	ROUTE('POST /upload/', myupload, ['upload'], 1024); // 1024 kB = max. request size

};

function myupload() {
	var self = this;

	// "self.files" contains Array of HttpFile
	// Look to "HttpFile" documentation
	console.log(self.files);

	self.success();
}
```

## File routing

File routing processes static files, which can be generated dynamically. File routing is a bit different because it's optimized for the performance. All files are processed via the `GET` method only.

- [File example](#)
- [Example with image resizing](#)

```js
ROUTE('FILE /relative/url/*.jpg', action_fn, [flags]);
RESIZE('/pictures/*.jpg', convertor_fn, [flags]);
```

- `path/*.*` processes all files
- `path/*.jpg` processes only files with `jpg` extension

__All files__:

```js
// Example
// File: /controllers/example.js

exports.install = function() {
	ROUTE('FILE /documents/*.*', handle_documents);
	ROUTE('FILE /images/*.jpg',  handle_images);
};

function handle_documents(req, res) {
	// "req" -> read more in "Request.prototype"
	// "res" -> read more in "Response.prototype"
	// your code
	res.file('/path/to/file.pdf');
}

function handle_images(req, res) {
	// "req" -> read more in "Request.prototype"
	// "res" -> read more in "Response.prototype"
	// your code
}
```

__Images only__:

```js
// Example
// File: /controllers/example.js

exports.install = function() {
	RESIZE('/gallery/*.jpg', resize);
};

function resize(image) {
	image.resize(120, 120);
	image.quality(90);
	image.minify();
}
```

Images are resized and saved to the temporary directory so that you won't modify original filenames.

## WebSocket routing

```js
// Example
// File: /controllers/example.js

exports.install = function() {
	ROUTE('SOCKET /', socket, ['text']); // "text" means only plain text communication
};

function socket() {

	// this === Controller
	var self = this;

	// Automaticaly destroys the controller after all clients disconnect
	self.autodestroy();

	self.on('open', function(client) {
		client.send('Hello world');
	});

	self.on('close', function(client) {
		client.send('Bye Bye!');
	});

	self.on('message', function(client, message) {
		console.log(message);
	});

}
```

__Dynamic routing__:

```js
// Example
// File: /controllers/example.js

exports.install = function() {
	ROUTE('SOCKET /{room}/', socket); // Data will be serialized/deserialized in JSON
};

function socket(room) {

	// "room" {String}
	console.log(room);

	// this === Controller
	var self = this;

	// Automaticaly destroys the controller after all clients disconnect
	self.autodestroy();

	self.on('open', function(client) {
		client.send({ msg: 'Hello world' });
	});

	self.on('close', function(client) {
		client.send({ msg: 'Bye Bye!' });
	});

	self.on('message', function(client, message) {
		console.log(message);
	});

}
```

