The call function is a global alternative for [instance.call](/total4/5aed2001pj51c/#10892e001rt61c).
`this` is a reference to [FlowStreamInstance](/total4/5aed1001bj51c/#)
```javascript
exports.call = function(data, callback) {
	// this === {FlowStreamInstance}
};
```

Optional. This delegate is executed from the client using `data.call` function shown bellow.
```javascript
instance.call = function(data, callback) {
    callback('Hello world');
};
```
To call this function from client use this:
```javascript
ON('configure_<component-name>', function(data) {
	data.call(/*{ name: 'outputs' },*/ function(response) {
		console.log(response); // 'Hello world'
	}/*, true*/);
});
```
The `data.call` function takes the following arguments:
- `data` - optional, any data you might want to use on the server
- `callback` - required, will be called when data arrives back from the server
- `true` - optional, if true, exports.call will be used on the server instead of instance.call

- `Flow` means a created `FlowStream` instance
- `FlowComponent` means a declaration of a component
- `FlowInstance` is a created instance from a component declaration
- `FlowMessage` is an object which is created from all `.send()` methods whithin FlowStream

::: Example: JS declaration

```js
flowstream.register('reverse', function(instance) {

	// instance.inputs = [{ id: 'input', name: 'My input' }];
	// instance.outputs = [{ id: 'output', name: 'My output' }];

	// Optional
	instance.open = function(next) {
		// Instance is opening
		// next() {Function}
	};

	instance.close = function() {
		// Instance is closed
	};

	instance.message = function($) {

		// $ {Message}

		var arr = $.data.split('');
		arr.reverse();
		$.data = arr.join('');

		// Sends data to output named "output"
		// see instance.outputs above
		$.send('output');

	};

});
```
:::

::: Example: HTML declaration

- Can be registered via [`flow.add(name, body)`](/total4/5aed1001bj51c/#61ecf001nm51c) method

