This method makes a backup of a specific directory. The file structure is the same as the Total.js Bundle / Package file (plain text file). For the restoring, you need to use `RESTORE()` method.

```js
BACKUP(filename, directory, callback, [filter]);
// @filename {String} a backup filename, must contain absolute path
// @directory {String} a directory for backing up
// @callback {Function(err, response)}
//	@err {ErrorHandling}
//	@response {Object} in the form { filename: String, files: Number, size: Number }
// @filter {Function(path, isdirectory)} optional, must return Boolean ("true" will include file)
```

__Example__:

```js
BACKUP(PATH.root('backup.txt'), PATH.databases(), function(err, response) {
	console.log(response);
});
```

This method restores backup file created by the `BACKUP()` method.

```js
RESTORE(filename, target, callback, [filter]);
// @filename {String} a backup filename, must contain absolute path
// @target {String} a directory, where the files will be restored
// @callback {Function(err, response)}
//	@err {ErrorHandling}
//	@response {Object} in the form { filename: String, files: Number, size: Number }
// @filter {Function(path, isdirectory)} optional, must return Boolean ("true" will extract file)
```

__Example__:

```js
RESTORE(PATH.root('backup.txt'), PATH.databases(), function(err, response) {
	console.log(response);
});
```

