The method returns a display size for the `window` or a specific element:

- `xs` extra small display (mobile phone)
- `sm` small display (tablet)
- `md` medium display (laptop)
- `lg` large display (desktop computer)

The size is calculated according to the [`DEF.devices`](/components/61458001di51c/#61bb8001di51c) property.

```js
WIDTH([element]);
// @element {jQuery/HTMLelement} optional
// returns {String}
```

The method is a better alternative to `EXEC()` method because it implements async/await and better handling of additional arguments.

```js
CALL(schema|action, [model]);
// @schema|action {String} Schema or Action name
// @model {Object} optional
// returns {Caller}
```

__Caller__:

```js
var caller = CALL('Users --> find');
// or
// var caller = CALL('action_name');

// Sets additional params (key/value and values must be string)
caller.params(object);

// Sets additional query arguments (key/value and values must be string)
caller.query(object);

// Sets user instance to the action
caller.user(object);

// Assings a controller
caller.controller(object);

// A callback
caller.callback(function(err, response) {});

// Returns promise
caller.promise([$]);
```

### Examples

__Without model__:

```js
var users = await CALL('Users --> find').query({ page: '1', sort: 'name_asc' }).promise();
// or
// CALL('Users --> find').query({ page: '1', sort: 'name_asc' }).callback(console.log);
```

__With a model__:

```js
await CALL('Users --> update', { name: 'Peter' }).params({ userid: '123456' }).promise();
await CALL('Users --> insert', { name: 'Peter' }).promise();
```

__Multiple operations__:

```js
await CALL('Users --> check update (response) notify', { name: 'Peter' }).params({ userid: '123456' }).promise();
```

- if you don't use the model, then the framework will skip the validation
- if you don't use `(response)` then the output will be object with actions name, e.g.:

```js
{
	check: Object,
	updated: Object,
	notify: Object
}
```

This method tries to find `input,textarea,select`.

```js
self.autofocus([selector]);
// @selector {String} optional, default: "input,textarea,select"
// returns {Component}
```

This method creates audit log.

```js
$.audit($, message, [type]);
// $ {Object} SchemaInstance/Controller
// @message {String} required
// @type {String} optional, can contain "info" (default), "warning", "error" or "success"
```

The `message` argument can contain dynamic variables:

- `{user.key}` reads a value from the user session
- `{data.key}` reads a value from insert/update data
- `{model.key}` reads a value from the model
- `{query.key}` reads a value from the query URL arguments
- `{params.key}` reads a value from the routing params

__Example__:

```js
schema.setInsert(function($, model) {
	DB().insert('tbl_log', model).audit($, 'Shut up and take my money!').callback($.done());
});
```

